The paper discusses trajectory optimization for robotics tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves learning to adapt the parameters of the Gaussian Process Motion Planning (GPMP) algorithm, which involves machine learning techniques such as differentiable optimization and end-to-end training, suggesting that it could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of GPMP for motion planning also involves control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) to some extent.
